body_html:
@rmlarsen I ran the benchmarks again two more times and got much better results (make sure to scroll over if the pixel results are hidden):

Run 1:

Relative change in percent:
                              	  nexus-5	 nexus-5x	  nexus-6	 nexus-6p	    pixel
           facenet-v8-stripped	-14.49978	 -1.32524	 -3.33963	 -2.77208	 -6.87099
                  inception-v1	 58.87876	  5.66264	  3.67781	 -2.78782	-16.60963
                  inception-v3	 27.62776	 -0.03850	  4.21516	  1.79008	  0.39579
               multibox-person	 -7.51846	 17.31707	 32.65962	-10.62376	 -8.44006
       ssd-mobilenet-v1-person	-29.54936	 -0.88066	  6.12411	  3.71565	 -4.09103
                       stylize	-28.55930	 -7.68450	 -6.32689	 19.17275	 -6.02302
             stylize-quantized	-15.68737	 -2.59237	  4.23402	 18.88487	 -6.51874
                      wordlens	 67.26827	202.31065	 -0.73515	  0.69556	 -0.38815

Run 2:

Relative change in percent:
                              	  nexus-5	 nexus-5x	  nexus-6	 nexus-6p	    pixel
           facenet-v8-stripped	 35.86868	 -5.92455	 -4.43560	  4.27805	 -3.76654
                  inception-v1	 -5.30476	  2.79366	-13.61444	  1.77188	-17.61543
                  inception-v3	 -5.92321	 -0.65455	 -2.57162	 -1.41027	  0.92794
               multibox-person	-23.50986	 -0.06107	  5.29944	 -2.18944	-11.09237
       ssd-mobilenet-v1-person	 36.09077	-18.27276	 -0.10371	  1.09788	 -2.32616
                       stylize	 -6.52473	 -8.29781	 -0.80654	 18.24873	 -8.23492
             stylize-quantized	 28.76460	  1.34093	 -0.11584	 13.73769	 -5.18219
                      wordlens	-28.47009	 -0.14812	-11.14184	 41.61584	  6.06806

Not sure what the difference was from the initial test, maybe I had some conflating factor previously -- made extra sure to isolate the change this time around. Seems worth commiting.

The couple of spikes in timing could be down to getting warm devices that hit thermal throttling during the tests, as most of them only exist in a single run. The only device which got consistently worse was the 6p, everything else got some decent gains.
